The new species comes close to A. dendrophilus (
Weingaertner 1950
) Massey 1966 in most morphometric characteristics but differs in having smaller 'a' value (13.0-19.6 vs 23.3-30.7) in males; smaller 'b' value (5.7-6.3 vs 6.8-8.6) in females; greater 'c' (3.1-3.6 vs 2.0-3.0) and 'V' (43.0-46.9 vs 33.7-36.7) values; labial sensilla papilliform (vs setose); males with broad, massive (vs slender, arcuate) spicules; hood-shaped (vs rounded) capitula; spicules having prominent dorsal and ventral arms (vs arms not demarcated) and genital papillae ten pairs (vs eight pairs) in A. dendrophilus apud Gagarin 2002 .
